Package org.phlo.tuplez.operation

Interface Summary
GeneratesKey<KeyType extends Number> Marks implementation of Operation as generating key values of type KeyType.
Operation<InputType,OutputType> Operation is base Interface which must be implemented by all classes representing concrete database operations (i.e.
OperationInput<InputType> Specifies a Operation's InputType.
OperationOutput<OutputType> Specifies a Operation's OutputType.
ReturnsSingleRow Marks implementation of Operation as single-row returning.
StatementIsComputed<InputType> Marks implementation of Operation as having a SQL statement which depends on the input parameter an can therefore not be specified by an annotation.
 

Annotation Types Summary
KeyColumn Specified the column containg the generated key.
OutputColumn Overrides the OutputType's getter a given column is mapped to and the JDBC ResultSet accessor used to fetch that column's values.
OutputMapping Contains a list of OutputColumns, each mapping a certain result row to an OutputType getter and a ResultSet accessor.
Statement Specified the underlying statement of Operations.
